author: Aylin Woodward
title: The coronavirus probably started spreading in Wuhan far earlier than Chinese authorities reported — here's the more likely timeline
description: Authorities in Wuhan, China, reported 41 cases of an mysterious, pneumonialike respiratory illness to the World Health Organization on December 31. Most were linked to a local wet market. Three months later, that illness — now known as COVID-19 — has infected…
content:
Authorities in Wuhan, China, first informed the World Health Organization about an unknown, pneumonialike illness on December 31.
